[{"location":"#CUBE","page":"Home","title":"CUBE","text":"Documentation for CUBE.\n\nRead and write Gaussian cube files from Julia. For now just a rudimentary proof of principle implementation.","category":"section"},{"location":"#Examples","page":"Home","title":"Examples","text":"Reading data works like this:\n\nusing CUBE\n\ncube = CUBE.read(\"water.cube\")\n\nThe resulting CubeFile struct holds the information about the molecular structure (cube.system) or the data stored in the cube file (cube.data).\n\nSaving is just the reverse process, i.e. storing such a struct to disk:\n\nusing CUBE\nCUBE.save(\"water.cube\", cube)","category":"section"},{"location":"#References","page":"Home","title":"References","text":"http://paulbourke.net/dataformats/cube/\nhttps://h5cube-spec.readthedocs.io/en/latest/cubeformat.html\nhttp://gaussian.com/cubegen/\n\n","category":"section"}]
